<div class="content-item other-content">
        <!-- START statement -->
        <div class="statement col-md-9  content-container " id='contribution-63f646e8-cece-4de8-9c35-81c786495d89'>
            
<p class="">46.</p>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            </div>
        <div class="clearfix"></div>
        <!-- END statement -->
</div><div class="content-item" id="contribution-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
                Sir Ralph Glyn
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1942-09-10/debates/c9d0e1af-2dfb-4a4b-9a84-df4e97b44cc0/CombinedOperations(QuestionsToMinisters)#contribution-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">asked the Prime Minister whether the Secretary of State for War, the First Lord of the Admiralty and the Secretary of State for Air are answerable to this House for the conduct of soldiers, sailors and airmen and their stores and equipment, in operations planned and carried out by Combined Operations Staff; and, if not, which Minister will answer?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1942-09-10/debates/c9d0e1af-2dfb-4a4b-9a84-df4e97b44cc0/CombinedOperations(QuestionsToMinisters)#contribution-01ecf55f-7e53-458a-a2d2-3fd50964bd03">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
                The Prime Minister (Mr. Churchill)
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1942-09-10/debates/c9d0e1af-2dfb-4a4b-9a84-df4e97b44cc0/CombinedOperations(QuestionsToMinisters)#contribution-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">The answer to the first part of the Question is in the affirmative so far as specific details are concerned. But the main responsibility for operations is borne by the War Cabinet and the Minister of Defence.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1942-09-10/debates/c9d0e1af-2dfb-4a4b-9a84-df4e97b44cc0/CombinedOperations(QuestionsToMinisters)#contribution-8523e2f1-af19-462c-9a01-e28305bf21fd">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-64d2d32d-1fd8-4240-a0f9-c3c5090b9f8f">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-64d2d32d-1fd8-4240-a0f9-c3c5090b9f8f">
